A '''didactic method''' ({{lang-el|didáskein}}, ''to teach''; lore of teaching) is a [[teaching method]] that follows a consistent scientific approach or educational style to engage the student’s mind.
The didactic method of instruction is often contrasted with [[dialectics]] and the [[Socratic method]]; the term can also be used to refer to a specific didactic method, as for instance [[Constructivist teaching methods|constructivist didactics]].
{{ژباړل}}
Didactics is the theory of teaching and, in a wider sense, the theory and practical application of [[teaching]] and [[learning]].
In demarcation from "[[Mathetics]]" (the science of learning), didactics refers only to the science of teaching.

This theory might be contrasted with [[Open learning]], in which people can learn by themselves, in an unstructured manner, on topics of interest.

